A 28-year old will appear in the Protea Magistrates court for his alleged involvement in the death of a 41-year old woman. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A 28-year old will appear in the Protea Magistrates Court on Tuesday for his alleged involvement in the death of a 41-year old woman. The woman was found buried in a shallow grave in a shack in Vlakfontein. READ: Woman's body found under boyfriend's bed in Vlakfontein The suspect is believed to have confessed to the murder. Gauteng Safety MEC, Faith Mazibuko visited the crime scene on Monday and said the department will seek to track down the deceased's family. Mazibuko is also expected to attend today's [Tuesday] brief court proceedings.